<style>
  .article_column-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 320px;
    border-radius: 11px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 50%;
  }
  .article_column {
      height: max-content;
  }
  .article_column-third {
    width: calc(33.3333334% - 33.3333334px);
  }
  @media(max-width: 1450px) {
    .article_column-third {
      width: calc(33.3333334% - 20px);
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
      gap: 30px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 1250px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: calc(50% - 15px);
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 750px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: 100%;
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
        gap: 40px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 450px) {
    .article_column-image {
      height: 250px;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="block-flex-wrap block-flex-center-center block-gap-15 block-max-width tac m-auto">
    <h2 class="h2-heading-ss">
      How to Tell if a Hermès Bag Is Real: 
      <span class="h2-heading-pp">
        Key Signs of Counterfeit Hermès Handbags
      </span>
    </h2>
    <p class="body-text">
        Spotting a fake Hermès bag can be difficult, especially with counterfeiters getting better at mimicking the luxury brand’s iconic styles. However, there are still several signs that can help you perform a basic Hermès authenticity check before turning to a professional service. Whether you're researching how to authenticate a Hermès bag or just trying to avoid a costly mistake, here are some of the most reliable indicators of a counterfeit Hermès handbag:
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-center">
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "hermes-seo_examples-1.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Spotting fake Hermes bag: Inferior Leather Quality">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 1</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Inferior Leather Quality</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Authentic Hermès bags — especially Birkins and Kellys — are crafted from premium leathers like Togo, Epsom, and Clemence. Fake bags often feel overly stiff or plasticky, and may have a chemical smell. If the leather doesn’t feel luxurious, it probably isn’t.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "hermes-seo_examples-2.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Spotting fake Hermes bag: Incorrect Hermès Stamping">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 2</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Incorrect Hermès Stamping</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          The logo should read <strong>“Hermès Paris Made in France”</strong> and be evenly aligned, with clear, crisp font. Learn <strong>how to check the Hermès stamp</strong> carefully — it should be properly embossed and not printed. Uneven letters or faded print are immediate red flags.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "hermes-seo_examples-3.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Spotting fake Hermes bag: Misplaced or Flimsy Hardware">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 3</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Misplaced or Flimsy Hardware</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Hermès uses high-quality, heavy metal hardware, often plated with gold or palladium. The engraved markings should be clean and sharp, not etched poorly. Counterfeit hardware may feel light, chip easily, or be the wrong color tone.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "hermes-seo_examples-4.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Spotting fake Hermes bag: Incorrect or Missing Date Codes">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 4</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Incorrect or Missing Date Codes</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Every Hermès bag has a date stamp and a craftsman's code, usually hidden on the interior. Use a <strong>Hermès serial number lookup</strong> or <strong>Hermès code checker</strong> to cross-check the authenticity. Missing, misplaced, or incorrect stamps are a common counterfeit sign.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "hermes-seo_examples-5.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Spotting fake Hermes bag: Uneven Stitching">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 5</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Uneven Stitching</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Hermès artisans use saddle stitching — done by hand, not machine — for incredible durability and aesthetic. Sloppy, irregular, or loose stitches indicate poor craftsmanship and likely mean the bag is not genuine.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

